cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with the security of communication networks, specifically the Tor network, against selective denial-of-service (DoS) attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network infrastructure and communication protocols, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the second likely category. The paper also discusses the overhead of the detection algorithm, which could fall under the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and simulation, which could fall under the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with anonymity and privacy, which could fall under the category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
